4 This study (modified after
Mabuchi et al. 2014
)

Colour in alcohol (
Fig. 1C
): body creamy white with no other markings; fins mostly clear, but tips of branched principal caudal-fin rays with dark dots which extend anteriorly over two thirds of fin’s middle rays; several dark dots scattered on distal third of pelvic-fin rays; 5 dark dots in a vertical line on membrane between second and third dorsal-fin spines; dark dots scattered on occiput and on area between upper end of gill cover and first dorsal-fin origin; faint dark dots of various sizes loosely clustered posteriorly across caudal peduncle.
